The paper proposes a dataset for evaluating visual-inertial odometry approaches, which is relevant to the fields of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the evaluation of state-of-the-art approaches, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of motion capture systems and synchronization of sensors suggests a potential focus on control systems (cs.SY).
